## Who this is for

- New users with no prior Bastion knowledge.
- Experienced engineers who want copy/paste command paths.

## Quick start order

1. Read [General SSH use](./general-ssh.html).
2. Use [SSH port forwarding and services](./ssh-port-forwarding-and-services.html) for Artemis, Postgres, and Gerrit.
3. Use [Using Azure Portal](./using-azure-portal.html) for browser-based SSH/RDP path.
4. Use [Troubleshooting](./troubleshooting.html) when connection fails.
5. Check [Additional guidance via links](./additional-guidance-via-links.html) for product-level docs.

## Placeholder convention

All examples use obvious placeholders. Replace values before use.

- `<SUBSCRIPTION_NAME_OR_ID>`
- `<BASTION_NAME>`
- `<BASTION_RESOURCE_GROUP>`
- `<TARGET_VM_RESOURCE_GROUP>`
- `<TARGET_VM_NAME>`
- `<TARGET_VM_RESOURCE_ID>`
- `<ENTRA_USERNAME>`
- `<POSTGRES_FQDN>`
- `<GERRIT_HOSTNAME>`
- `<REPO_NAME>`
